The paper deals with the problem of shadow detection in images, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a new benchmark dataset for this task, which involves collecting and labeling a large number of images with shadows in various scenarios. This requires significant data processing and analysis, which could involve machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and statistical modeling (cs.LG). The authors also propose a new shadow detection network with a detail enhancement module, which involves image processing and computer graphics (cs.MM). Finally, the paper could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) since it deals with the problem of identifying and extracting relevant information (shadows) from images.
